		<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER" colspan="3">
		
		<h3><FONT FACE="ARIAL,HELVETICA">THE NEXT EMERIL, MARTHA STEWART OR IRON CHEF TO BE DISCOVERED TUESDAY NIGHT AT THE GALLERIA</font></H3>
		</TD></TR>
		<TR><TD>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		<TR><TD colspan="3">
		<FONT FACE="ARIAL,HELVETICA" SIZE="2"><B><I><FONT face=Arial>
<CENTER>Children Will Be Given the Opportunity To Be 'Chef for a Night' As Part of the Galleria Goes Gourmet Festivities
<P></I></FONT></CENTER><FONT face=Arial><FONT size=3>WHAT: </B>As part of the Galleria Goes Gourmet, Pluto&#8217;s Restaurant will be having 'Chef for a Night' activities for children ages one to twelve, in hopes of discovering the next Martha Stewart or Emeril. Children will be given a chef&#8217;s hat, apron and the opportunity to prepare their own meal. Also, during the Galleria Goes Gourmet festivities, there will be:</FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Arial>A special winemaker&#8217;s dinner at Birch Creek with wines from Lava Cap. </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Arial>Free samples of Birch Creek&#8217;s magnificent Caesar Salad. </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Arial>Sushi demonstrations and sampling at Rice &amp; Company. </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Arial>Music by jazz/funk group The Mind Club. </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Arial>Free samples provided by Godiva Chocolatier and Harry &amp; David. </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Arial>Other giveaways by Anchor Blue and Bare Escentuals.</FONT></LI></UL><B><FONT face=Arial>
<P>WHEN: </B>Tuesday, April 10, 2001</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Arial>6:00 pm to 8:00 pm</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Arial>(Demonstrations for the media will be available in advance of the event)</FONT></P><B><FONT face=Arial>
<P>WHERE: </B>Galleria at Roseville, Promenade Area<BR>1151 Galleria Boulevard<BR>Roseville, California</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Arial>Unique to the Sacramento region, Galleria at Roseville features <B>The Promenade </B>&#8211; an outdoor, pedestrian streetscape including upscale restaurants and distinctive retailers. Restaurants and stores located within the Promenade include <B>Birch Creek, Il Fornaio, Max&#8217;s Cafe, Rice &amp; Company Asian Bistro, Pluto&#8217;s, Borders Books Music Cafe, Copeland&#8217;s, Home Design, Pottery Barn, Restoration Hardware and Crate &amp; Barrel (opening May 2001). </B>The Promenade is designed as an urban village with street-side cafes, beautiful water features in a nature setting, a children&#8217;s play area and a fireplace. Galleria at Roseville features more then 120 retailers anchored by <B>Nordstrom</B>, <B>Macy&#8217;s</B>, <B>JCPenney</B> and <B>Sears.</P></B></FONT>
<P><FONT face=Arial>In addition to the Galleria Goes Gourmet festivities, the Galleria is featuring strolling musicians every weekend this spring and summer. The bands will cover a myriad of musical styles including Jazz, Bluegrass, Dixieland, Cajun, Latin, Mariachi and more.</FONT></P></FONT>
<P><FONT face=Arial size=2>Galleria at Roseville is owned and developed by Chicago-based Urban Shopping Centers, Inc. (NYSE: URB), a self-administered real estate investment trust (REIT), which is in the business of owning, acquiring, managing, leasing, developing and redeveloping super-regional and regional malls. The company opened Brandon TownCenter in Tampa, Florida in February 1995, Wolfchase Galleria in Memphis, Tennessee in February 1997, a second Tampa-area mall, Citrus Park Town Center, in March 1999, and expects to open Galleria at Roseville on August 25, 2000 and The Streets at Southpoint in Durham, North Carolina in spring 2002. Urban Shopping Centers, Inc. owns interests in several of the premier shopping centers in the United States including Oakbrook Center (Oak Brook, Illinois), Century City Shopping Center &amp; Marketplace (Los Angeles, California), Water Tower Place (Chicago, Illinois), Old Orchard Center (Skokie, Illinois), Copley Place (Boston, Massachusetts),San Francisco Shopping Centre (San Francisco, California), and The Galleria (Houston, Texas), as well as in Urban Retail Properties Co., its property management, leasing and development affiliate. Urban Retail Properties Co. is one of the nation's largest retail property managers, managing more than 59 million square feet of space in 26 states and the District of Columbia.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Arial size=2>For more information on Galleria at Roseville or to schedule an on-site interview, please contact Mitch Zak at (916) 446-6667.</FONT></P>
